This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentiment and style transfer, which are typically categorized under the arXiv sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a neural model to combine the extracted content words, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of retrieval methods to find new phrases associated with the target attribute, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of unsupervised learning, which falls under the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
